# Fallback identities for git over SSH.
#
# github.com and ddoghq.github.com are pinned by the managed git-config-tool
# config to its ghkeys with `IdentitiesOnly yes`, and those private keys live on
# the laptop — they reach a workspace only through the forwarded agent, which
# dies when the laptop sleeps (and can go stale inside a long-lived tmux). Naming
# our on-disk keys here appends them to each host's identity list (`IdentityFile`
# is additive; IdentitiesOnly still holds), so git keeps working with the agent
# gone. Each host maps to exactly one account, so there is no wrong-account risk:
#   github.com        -> tausman             (id_ed25519_tausman)
#   ddoghq.github.com -> tausif-rahman_ddog  (id_ed25519_ddog)
#
# This file is only read because install.sh adds `Include ~/.ssh/custom/*` to
# ~/.ssh/config (the workspace host has no workspaces-cli include of its own). The
# keypairs are generated per-machine by `install.sh auth` and never committed;
# only this static reference is version-controlled. Each key must be SSO-authorized
# for its org (install.sh walks you through that).
Host github.com
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_tausman

Host ddoghq.github.com
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_ddog
